<HEAD>Switzerland Faces Record Number of Asylum-Seekers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 13,000 people have asked for
asylum in Switzerland so far this year and the annual total is
expected to reach a record 25,000, government officials say.
   In a continuing trend, nearly half the new applicants are Turks,
followed by Tamils fleeing Sri Lanka, Justice Ministry spokesman
Maud Krafft said Thursday.
   Last year, a record 16,700 refugees applied for Swiss asylum.
   The Justice Ministry said 33,000 cases are pending.
   Justice minister Arnold Koller said the growing number of asylum
applicants has strained Switzerland's bureaucracy and refugeee
services ``to the limits of capacity.''
