<HEAD>Divorce on the Rise in South Korea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Divorce is on the rise and infidelity
is blamed in nearly half of the cases, according to court statistics
released today.
   Of the 20,345 cases filed with the Supreme Court in 1988, about
90 percent involved one to four children and 47.4 percent cited
infidelity for the breakup.
   For this year, the court said 27,778 cases alread had been filed
by the end of July.
   Family counselors say rising incomes, dual-career families and
the increased stress of urban living have contributed to the breakup
of marriages in a society in which divorce is still frowned upon.
   The court statistics showed that women filed almost half the
divorce cases.
</TEXT>
