<HEAD>Hitachi to Build Personal Computers in United States, Europe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hitachi Ltd., Japan's largest electrical machinery
maker, plans to build personal computers in the United States and
Europe, the company said Friday.
   Hitachi intends to produce personal computers and laptops to
expand its market share abroad, said spokesman Kazuya Hanazuka.
   Hitachi had focused its personal computer efforts on the Japanese
domestic market, of which it holds only a small share. Exports have
been ``almost nil,'' Hanazuka said.
   The company is still studying whether it will produce the
computers in its existing factories or in new ones, he said. No
other details were disclosed.
