<HEAD>Baker, Shevardadnze Meeting in Wyoming Set</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Secretary of State James A. Baker III and
Soviet Foreign Minister Eduard A. Shevardnadze will meet Sept. 22-23
at a lodge in the Grand Teton National Park outside Jackson, Wyo.,
the State Department said Friday.
   The meeting is designed to lay the groundwork for a summit
encounter between President Bush and Soviet President Mikhail S.
Gorbachev.
   State Department spokeswoman Margaret Tutwiler said topics will
include arms control, human rights and regional conflicts.
   Baker and Sheverdnadze agreed in Paris in late July to hold the
summit preparatory discussions in Wyoming, where Baker has a ranch.
At the July meeting, Baker had shown Shevardnadze pictures of the
area.
   Assuming the talks are successful, the summit meeting will be
scheduled, but it is unclear whether the summit will be possible
before the end of the year.
