<FIRST>r i AM-Refugees-Spies     09-01 0186</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Refugees-Spies,0191</SECOND>
<HEAD>Security Officials: East Germany Will Use Exodus To Plant Spies</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Refugees, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Security officials said Friday they
expected East Germany to use a mass exodus of refugees from Hungary
to slip agents into West Germany.
   The sources, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said the flight
of thousands of refugees provided an ``excellent opportunity'' to
funnel intelligence agents into West Germany.
   In addition to traditional espionage activities, the East German
government wants to learn more about the refugees themselves, how
they are treated in West Germany when they arrive, and how they
adjust to a new life in the West, security officials said.
   At least 6,000 East Germans have used Hungary's newly porous
border with Austria to flee to the West since the barbed-wire
barriers of the former Iron Curtain were dismantled beginning in May.
   West German government officials have indicated a mass transfer
of East Germans to West Germany from Hungary is being planned in the
next few days.
   As many as 20,000 East Germans in Hungary are expected to ask to
come to West Germany.
</TEXT>
