<HEAD>Metromedia Buys ITT Long-Distance Properties</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Metromedia Co. says it has completed the
acquisition of ITT Communications Services Inc. and ITT Chernow
Communications Inc. for an undisclosed price.
   The deal, announced in March, makes Metromedia Long Distance Inc.
the fifth largest long-distance carrier in the United States, after
American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co., MCI Communications Corp., US
Sprint Communications Co. and Telecom USA of Atlanta, which serves
the Southeast and Midwest.
   Metromedia Long Distance is based in Secaucus, N.J., and serves
markets in Texas, Florida and the New York-New Jersey area. The
company said Thursday the acquisition of ITT circuits would give it
greater national reach.
   The parent company, Metromedia Co., is privately owned, and its
majority partner is John W. Kluge, the president and chairman.
