<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     09-01 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0160</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Share Prices Firm At Midday, Trading Moderate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were firming at midday in London on
moderate volume as last-minute buying at the end of the current
trading account squeezed a number of the market's biggest stocks.
   Traders described the market as bullish but nervous. An
encouraging response by Wall Street to the U.S. August unemployment
figures due out today could lift the London market higher, they
said. However, worries about a battery of mid-year earnings results
due over the next two weeks will make any upward move tentative.
   Around midday, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100 share index
was up 10.0 points, or 0.4 percent, at 2,398.9, its highest level of
the session. The key index opened the day up 4.2 points and has
improved steadily since.
   The narrower FT-30 share index was up 10.4 points at 1,988.0.
Volume through midday was a moderate 265.9 million shares.
</TEXT>
