<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices soared to a 1989 high Friday in
improved volume with the FT-SE 100 index closing above the
2,400-point level.
   Buying after the opening of a new two-week trading account,
combined with strength in the New York market, helped propel the
London Stock Exchange beyond the psychologically important barrier.
   The FT-SE 100 closed up 19.6 points, or 0.82 percent, at 2,407.5.
   The FT-30 share index ended 15.1 points higher at 1,992.7. The FT
500 index was up 9.62 at 1,344.14.
   Volume totaled 531.4 million shares, up from 447.0 million
Thursday.
