<FILEID>AP-NR-09-01-89 2331EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Bolivia-Debt     09-01 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Bolivia-Debt,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bolivia Announces Agreement to Eliminate Debts to Argentina</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LA PAZ, Bolivia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Bolivian government has reached an
agreement to eliminate all its debt to Argentina, its principal
trading partner and creditor.
   Argentina will cancel $800 million owed to it by Bolivia, and in
return Bolivia will cancel $300 million that Argentina owes it for
natural gas purchases, Foreign Minister Carlos Iturralde announced.
   Bolivia has been paying $55 million a year in interest to
Argentina for funds that were largely borrowed during the 1980
right-wing military government headed by Luis Garcia Meza.
   ``With this agreement we are effectively lowering our debt $500
million, which represents 20 percent of our total debt,'' said
Iturralde.
</TEXT>
